    <title>Combined summary - Building a Bitcoin API and query system.</title>
    <updated>2023-06-13T14:18:44.711989+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2018-August/016323.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>A C++ and Node.js developer named Sumit Lahiri has proposed a new Bitcoin API that will allow for fast querying of Bitcoin blocks and transactions without requiring synchronization with all previous nodes. The proposal involves creating a standardized template containing minimal information about the actual mined block or transaction, which could greatly benefit web developers looking to create full-fledged Bitcoin explorer cum wallet systems on their end. However, some have concerns about the centralization of such an API and the need to trust third-party APIs rather than validating data independently.In response to these concerns, there is discussion about the use cases for block explorer-ish APIs, with some arguing that promoting decentralized services seems wise. Other tools and protocols, such as spruned, Bitcore, and Electrum servers, are also mentioned as potential solutions for fast querying of blockchain data. Jonas Schnelli emphasizes the importance of defining use-cases and being aware of consequences and downsides rather than advocating against a full-index block explorer-like API. Overall, the discussion highlights the need for decentralized solutions to avoid centralization and promote self-validation through the p2p network.The current centralized system for data storage is not very secure, which has led to the need for a decentralized solution. Ayms, an expert in the field, has provided several links to projects on GitHub that address this issue. These projects include Zcash wallets, Bitcoin wallets, dynamic blocklists, and anti-spies and private torrents. Zcash and Bitcoin wallets are designed to provide users with a high level of security and privacy when it comes to storing their cryptocurrency. Dynamic blocklists are used to prevent malicious actors from accessing certain resources or websites. Anti-spies and private torrents can also help protect user data and prevent unauthorized access. Overall, these projects offer potential solutions to the problem of insecure data storage. By utilizing decentralized technologies, individuals and organizations can improve their security and protect their sensitive information.</summary>
